Gunmen have attacked the P&F Filling Station, Nnokwa in the Idemili South Local Government Area of Anambra State, killing two persons on the spot. The incident happened on Saturday at the filling station, close to the St. Mary’s Catholic Church, Nnokwa. It was gathered that the gunmen shot the manager of the filling station, identified simply as Marvelous and his friend, also identified as Richard. The reason for the attack was still unknown as of the time of filing this report, but an eyewitness said both men, went to buy food to eat before they met their death. The eyewitness said, “Tears rolled down at Nnokwa this morning as both men, were gunned down by unknown gunmen. The manager of the filling station always sold diesel every Monday sit-at-home.” A video is currently circulating in the social media where a man was lying in a pool of blood and the head seen to have been blown bullets. Calls made to the mobile phone  of the state police spokesman, Ikenga Tochukwu, for official confirmation, were not picked and text messages sent to his phone were not also responded to as of the time of filing this report.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com